HEADWORD: Inkling
<hw>In"kling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A hint; an
intimation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The least <qex>inkling</qex> or glimpse of this island.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They had some <qex>inkling</qex> of secret messages.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inknee</ent>⟦br⟧
